  "text": "Although BRCA1 binds to DNA in a sequence-independent manner in vitro [CITATION_1] , in cells, it is most commonly found at DNA breaks associated with chromatin. Accordingly, we found that purified recombinant BRCA1/BARD1 bound nucleosome substrates in an electrophoretic mobility shift assay (EMSA) (Figures S1A-S1F). The binding was dynamic, as complexes were competed away by addition of unlabeled DNA ( Figure S1D ). This binding, along with the known structural similarities between the RING domains of BRCA1/BARD1 and those of the histone-H2A-specific ubiquitin ligase complex Polycomb repressive complex 1 (PRC1) Figure S1G) , prompted us to investigate whether BRCA1/BARD1 ubiquitylates nucleosomal histone proteins.",
